1
00:00:14,360 --> 00:00:17,440
♪In the airport lounge
at the break of day♪

2
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:22,240
♪A page of dust beneath my fingers♪

3
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:25,160
♪Filled with stories♪

4
00:00:25,160 --> 00:00:28,280
♪That others never got to tell♪

5
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,960
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

6
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:35,600
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

7
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,160
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

8
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:40,040
♪The world is split an inch wider♪

9
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,600
♪Raise your eyes, face the light♪

10
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:45,080
♪See the truth, and see the fright♪

11
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,800
♪Guard the crack within this door♪

12
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:52,600
♪Keep the way back home
always burning bright♪

13
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:57,040
♪The camera pans
across the boarding crowd♪

14
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:59,200
♪Some wear a smile,
some have their eyes adrift♪

15
00:00:59,280 --> 00:01:01,440
♪A red suitcase♪

16
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:05,360
♪Tied with faded pasts
and broken prayers♪

17
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:09,400
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

18
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:12,080
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

19
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:13,960
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

20
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:17,400
♪It's the heartbeat
echoing the call of law♪

21
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,000
[Gimlet Eyes]

22
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:32,960
[Episode 11]

23
00:01:33,680 --> 00:01:34,850
The only difference

24
00:01:34,870 --> 00:01:36,620
between a bus terminal plaza
and an airport inspection lane

25
00:01:37,150 --> 00:01:39,740
is that passengers here
come from every direction,

26
00:01:39,760 --> 00:01:40,820
not just straight ahead.

27
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:42,930
Then each of us takes one direction.

28
00:01:50,710 --> 00:01:52,050
At my three o'clock direction,

29
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:54,380
a guy is holding a bouquet of roses.

30
00:01:54,710 --> 00:01:56,180
Probably here to pick up his girlfriend.

31
00:01:57,840 --> 00:01:59,260
But he's been smiling

32
00:01:59,280 --> 00:02:01,050
at more than one girl
coming out of the terminal,

33
00:02:01,150 --> 00:02:02,690
even holding up the flowers
to signal them.

34
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:03,620
That means

35
00:02:03,640 --> 00:02:05,740
they've probably never met in person.

36
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:07,020
Perhaps an online relationship.
First in-person meeting.

37
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:09,340
Every girl he's approached

38
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:11,060
has long hair, a slim build,

39
00:02:11,150 --> 00:02:11,980
and trendy clothes

40
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:13,500
and is around 20 years old.

41
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:15,100
That matches Qian's description.

42
00:02:15,680 --> 00:02:17,410
Good chance he's seen her, too.

43
00:02:17,560 --> 00:02:18,540
Straight ahead of me,

44
00:02:18,910 --> 00:02:19,850
there's a minivan.

45
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:21,280
[Depart Every 30 Minutes]
The woman out front

46
00:02:21,280 --> 00:02:22,260
[from Chengnan Terminal Discount]
hustling for passengers

47
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:23,450
has probably seen Qian, too.

48
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:26,130
She only approaches
young women who are slim

49
00:02:26,190 --> 00:02:28,540
and look friendly.

50
00:02:28,870 --> 00:02:31,060
But once they look inside the van,

51
00:02:31,080 --> 00:02:31,820
they leave right away.

52
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:32,500
That means

53
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:34,660
there's probably only one seat left,

54
00:02:34,870 --> 00:02:36,340
and it's a cramped, uncomfortable one.

55
00:02:36,590 --> 00:02:37,410
She figures

56
00:02:37,430 --> 00:02:38,890
a slim girl can fit,

57
00:02:38,960 --> 00:02:41,170
and someone
who looks friendly won't argue much.

58
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:42,940
That fits Qian, too.

59
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:44,380
Worth checking.

60
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,010
At my two o'clock direction,

61
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:49,010
a middle-aged man in a gray tracksuit.

62
00:02:49,520 --> 00:02:50,780
If I'm reading this right,

63
00:02:51,190 --> 00:02:52,340
he's plainclothes police.

64
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:53,940
Broad shoulders, straight posture.

65
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:54,980
When he walks,

66
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:56,340
his neck stays upright,

67
00:02:56,430 --> 00:02:57,100
chin slightly tucked.

68
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:58,980
Years of military training.

69
00:02:59,190 --> 00:03:00,540
There's a tan line on his forehead

70
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:02,660
from wearing a peaked cap.

71
00:03:03,030 --> 00:03:04,130
It looks like he's waiting for someone,

72
00:03:04,150 --> 00:03:06,010
but he's actually watching

73
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:07,540
several young women
standing alone nearby.

74
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:10,170
All around 20,

75
00:03:10,430 --> 00:03:11,780
long hair, slim builds,

76
00:03:11,910 --> 00:03:12,780
and dressed stylishly.

77
00:03:13,310 --> 00:03:14,940
He keeps checking his phone
against them.

78
00:03:15,310 --> 00:03:15,890
That means

79
00:03:16,310 --> 00:03:18,540
that type of girl
is exactly what he's looking for today.

80
00:03:18,910 --> 00:03:21,410
Qian fits that profile.

81
00:03:21,470 --> 00:03:23,380
I'd say he's seen her.

82
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:26,410
Alright, we've got our leads.

83
00:03:26,470 --> 00:03:28,010
Show the photo and start checking.

84
00:03:28,590 --> 00:03:28,940
Yes, sir.

85
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:29,730
Yes, sir.

86
00:03:36,280 --> 00:03:37,780
This time, Qian…

87
00:03:37,910 --> 00:03:39,540
She was being too playful.

88
00:03:39,710 --> 00:03:40,290
When she gets back,

89
00:03:40,310 --> 00:03:41,940
I'll have a serious talk with her.

90
00:03:45,470 --> 00:03:47,010
I've been in Customs for a long time.

91
00:03:48,280 --> 00:03:49,450
I'm very clear

92
00:03:50,630 --> 00:03:51,540
whether she was being playful.

93
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:55,010
Why do you always assume the worst?

94
00:03:58,030 --> 00:04:00,290
When's her dad getting back?

95
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:02,410
Probably on his way.

96
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:32,660
Any luck?

97
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:34,170
Did you find anything?

98
00:04:34,190 --> 00:04:34,700
Yeah.

99
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:36,020
I showed the guy with the roses

100
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:37,140
Qian's photo.

101
00:04:37,310 --> 00:04:38,370
He remembered her.

102
00:04:38,630 --> 00:04:39,540
Said Qian seemed

103
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:41,050
to be with a foreign guy.

104
00:04:41,160 --> 00:04:41,610
They were rushing

105
00:04:41,630 --> 00:04:43,660
to catch a flight to Vancouver.

106
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:45,460
A foreign man heading to Vancouver?

107
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:46,490
Qian just got back from there.

108
00:04:46,510 --> 00:04:47,370
Why would she leave again?

109
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:48,810
I talked to the van lady.

110
00:04:48,830 --> 00:04:50,290
She'd seen Qian, too.

111
00:04:50,310 --> 00:04:51,730
But Qian didn't take her van.

112
00:04:51,750 --> 00:04:52,730
She took a cab.

113
00:04:52,950 --> 00:04:54,460
Before she got in, she answered a call

114
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:55,410
and spoke in a foreign language.

115
00:04:55,430 --> 00:04:56,460
It sounded like she was heading

116
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:58,140
to the Ponoliva Hotel
on the east side of the town.

117
00:04:58,560 --> 00:04:59,660
Qian studies abroad.

118
00:04:59,750 --> 00:05:00,900
Her English is definitely good.

119
00:05:00,920 --> 00:05:02,980
That lead is probably related to her.

120
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:06,050
Mentor, what did you get?

121
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:07,700
I talked to the plainclothes officer.

122
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:08,850
He did see Qian.

123
00:05:09,070 --> 00:05:10,850
She was alone with two suitcases.

124
00:05:11,630 --> 00:05:12,730
She even asked him for directions

125
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:16,140
to the new Jiangpanyuan guesthouse area.

126
00:05:17,240 --> 00:05:19,170
Police officers are specially trained.

127
00:05:19,190 --> 00:05:21,100
His info is probably the most reliable.

128
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:22,980
We can't drop a single lead.

129
00:05:23,070 --> 00:05:24,170
Time to split up.

130
00:05:24,830 --> 00:05:25,340
Dayu,

131
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:26,340
head back to the airport.

132
00:05:26,750 --> 00:05:27,980
The last flight

133
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:29,700
to Vancouver should be at 9 PM.

134
00:05:30,160 --> 00:05:30,810
We still have time.

135
00:05:31,040 --> 00:05:31,980
On the way,

136
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:32,980
call Zhang Weimin in Section III.

137
00:05:33,310 --> 00:05:34,930
Tell him to keep an eye on departures.

138
00:05:34,950 --> 00:05:35,340
Yes.

139
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:36,170
Shihuo,

140
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:38,610
Ponoliva is a chain hotel.

141
00:05:38,920 --> 00:05:40,290
They've got several locations
on the east side.

142
00:05:40,720 --> 00:05:43,730
You and Bowen start with the closest one
and work your way out.

143
00:05:44,750 --> 00:05:45,220
Zhang Yu,

144
00:05:45,270 --> 00:05:46,730
you and I will check Jiangpanyuan.

145
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:48,410
Everyone,

146
00:05:48,510 --> 00:05:49,580
stay in constant contact.

147
00:05:49,950 --> 00:05:51,930
The second you spot Qian
and her boyfriend,

148
00:05:51,950 --> 00:05:52,610
hold them there.

149
00:05:52,750 --> 00:05:53,930
If you can't handle it,

150
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:54,700
call the police.

151
00:05:54,830 --> 00:05:55,660
Call the police?

152
00:05:55,750 --> 00:05:57,580
Desperate times
call for desperate measures.

153
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:07,850
Mentor,

154
00:06:08,270 --> 00:06:09,660
this area's huge.

155
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:10,580
How do we find her?

156
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:13,610
We're not familiar with this area,

157
00:06:13,870 --> 00:06:15,140
and Qian definitely knows it even less.

158
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:16,580
If we want to find her,

159
00:06:16,870 --> 00:06:18,700
we have to think the way she would.

160
00:06:24,950 --> 00:06:27,780
This shop is the closest one
to the bus stop.

161
00:06:27,780 --> 00:06:28,360
[Jiangpanyuan Central Station]

162
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:28,970
[Jiangpanyuan Central Station]
She would've asked

163
00:06:28,970 --> 00:06:29,810
[Jiangpanyuan Central Station]
for directions here first.

164
00:06:30,120 --> 00:06:31,250
Maybe I'll go ask here.

165
00:06:31,270 --> 00:06:32,220
Alright, go ahead.

166
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:32,780
I'll park and follow.

167
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:33,220
Okay.

168
00:06:49,190 --> 00:06:49,780
Over here.

169
00:06:52,070 --> 00:06:54,610
One more block,
and we're out of the area.

170
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:57,050
But I double-checked
with the shop owner.

171
00:06:57,160 --> 00:06:57,850
He said

172
00:06:58,190 --> 00:07:00,460
Qian was supposed
to keep going down this road

173
00:07:00,630 --> 00:07:03,610
and turn up at the intersection ahead
before she…

174
00:07:09,950 --> 00:07:11,250
It looks like this area

175
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:12,460
was just a cover.

176
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:14,290
Where Qian's really headed

177
00:07:14,510 --> 00:07:15,580
is somewhere else.

178
00:07:15,580 --> 00:07:18,720
[Deep Water Warning Danger]

179
00:07:25,510 --> 00:07:26,020
Come with me.

180
00:07:30,360 --> 00:07:31,460
Shield me a bit.

181
00:07:35,190 --> 00:07:36,780
Is she waiting for someone?

182
00:07:37,480 --> 00:07:39,460
She's not focused on any one direction.

183
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:41,170
Probably not waiting.

184
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:42,580
She might just be tired.

185
00:07:42,720 --> 00:07:43,700
Taking a breather.

186
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:45,810
Should we go over?

187
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:46,850
Not yet.

188
00:07:47,160 --> 00:07:49,660
I want to see where she's really going.

189
00:07:50,920 --> 00:07:51,410
Here's the plan.

190
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:53,100
She knows me,

191
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:53,980
but not you.

192
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:55,140
You follow her.

193
00:07:55,430 --> 00:07:56,700
I'll stay behind both of you.

194
00:07:56,920 --> 00:07:57,410
Got it.

195
00:09:03,550 --> 00:09:04,130
Hi there.

196
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:05,820
What can I do for you?

197
00:09:07,320 --> 00:09:07,940
A manicure.

198
00:09:08,630 --> 00:09:10,340
[Garbage Sorting Guide]
The nail techs are all out for dinner.

199
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:13,220
You may come back in a bit
if you want one.

200
00:09:13,790 --> 00:09:15,250
I'll just browse the designs first.

201
00:09:15,550 --> 00:09:16,060
Sure.

202
00:09:16,270 --> 00:09:17,770
Over there. Take your time.

203
00:09:23,030 --> 00:09:25,100
So what can you do right now?

204
00:09:25,480 --> 00:09:26,940
I can only do basic nail care.

205
00:09:27,390 --> 00:09:28,850
Okay, I'll take that.

206
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:30,250
Okay, just a moment.

207
00:09:45,270 --> 00:09:45,730
Hands, please.

208
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:50,610
Sorry!

209
00:09:50,630 --> 00:09:51,530
Was it too hot?

210
00:09:52,030 --> 00:09:53,460
It's fine. I wasn't paying attention.

211
00:10:00,510 --> 00:10:02,300
Are you a police officer?

212
00:10:04,510 --> 00:10:05,610
Wh-what did you say?

213
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:09,340
I saw you watching that girl outside
the whole time.

214
00:10:09,440 --> 00:10:10,700
You're working on a case, right?

215
00:10:15,550 --> 00:10:17,130
I see all kinds of people here.

216
00:10:17,360 --> 00:10:20,530
At your age, you don't wear any jewelry.

217
00:10:20,630 --> 00:10:22,700
Plus, your hands
are kind of rough and dry.

218
00:10:22,840 --> 00:10:23,980
What else could you be if not a cop?

219
00:10:25,790 --> 00:10:27,490
Don't worry. I'll fully cooperate.

220
00:10:30,670 --> 00:10:32,610
What did that girl do?

221
00:10:32,720 --> 00:10:33,980
She looks so young.

222
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,060
Well, since you figured it out,

223
00:10:38,080 --> 00:10:39,060
I won't deny it.

224
00:10:39,510 --> 00:10:40,850
But there are things I can't tell you.

225
00:10:40,870 --> 00:10:41,650
Don't push it.

226
00:10:41,870 --> 00:10:42,650
Sure, I know.

227
00:10:42,670 --> 00:10:43,650
You've got rules.

228
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:46,460
Let me ask you something.

229
00:10:46,790 --> 00:10:49,250
Does that complex
over there have guesthouses?

230
00:10:49,390 --> 00:10:50,850
Yeah, quite a few actually.

231
00:10:51,030 --> 00:10:51,730
Most of the owners there

232
00:10:51,750 --> 00:10:53,180
are from out of town.

233
00:10:53,360 --> 00:10:54,300
Lots of small units.

234
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:56,180
So they only come for holidays.

235
00:10:56,750 --> 00:10:57,580
The rest of the time,

236
00:10:57,600 --> 00:10:59,530
they leave them with a housekeeper
for short-term rental.

237
00:11:00,150 --> 00:11:02,460
Before this area was developed,

238
00:11:02,510 --> 00:11:04,100
this was where most tourists stayed.

239
00:11:04,390 --> 00:11:05,530
So how does check-in work?

240
00:11:05,550 --> 00:11:06,770
Do you contact the housekeeper?

241
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:07,420
No.

242
00:11:07,440 --> 00:11:08,420
It's all online.

243
00:11:08,550 --> 00:11:10,820
You pay, and they send you
the door code. That's it.

244
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:11,940
You never even meet the housekeeper.

245
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:19,180
I need to go.

246
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:20,060
How much do I owe you?

247
00:11:20,360 --> 00:11:22,130
Forget the money. Just go!

248
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:24,130
I-I'll come back and pay you later.

249
00:11:24,150 --> 00:11:24,940
Alright, be careful!

250
00:11:28,150 --> 00:11:28,650
Mentor.

251
00:11:28,790 --> 00:11:29,980
Qian went into the complex.

252
00:11:30,030 --> 00:11:31,130
There are guesthouses in there.

253
00:11:57,270 --> 00:11:58,010
Which floor?

254
00:11:58,390 --> 00:11:59,530
Sixteenth, thanks.

255
00:12:22,150 --> 00:12:23,530
Sorry!

256
00:12:23,670 --> 00:12:24,940
My hand slipped. I didn't mean to…

257
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:25,700
- So sorry. - It's fine.

258
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:26,490
I was distracted.

259
00:12:26,870 --> 00:12:28,060
D-did it splash on you?

260
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:28,940
Let me wipe that for you.

261
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:29,610
It's fine, really, no need.

262
00:12:29,630 --> 00:12:30,730
Which room are you in?
I can come by later…

263
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:31,850
No, really, it's fine.

264
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:56,420
Mentor.

265
00:12:56,440 --> 00:12:57,650
Building 4, 16th floor.

266
00:13:01,390 --> 00:13:01,980
Mentor.

267
00:13:02,510 --> 00:13:03,010
Over here.

268
00:13:12,870 --> 00:13:14,490
Looks like that herbal tea
wasn't enough.

269
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:31,370
You need to tell me what's wrong.

270
00:13:31,550 --> 00:13:32,650
What happened?

271
00:13:36,630 --> 00:13:38,820
James, I'm telling you,

272
00:13:39,150 --> 00:13:41,650
if you don't show up soon,

273
00:13:41,910 --> 00:13:44,300
I'm throwing your suitcase away.

274
00:13:46,150 --> 00:13:46,980
Is it Qian?

275
00:13:50,550 --> 00:13:51,340
Who is it?

276
00:13:53,150 --> 00:13:54,220
Housekeeper.

277
00:13:59,270 --> 00:14:00,100
It's you.

278
00:14:00,320 --> 00:14:01,180
You're the housekeeper.

279
00:14:01,510 --> 00:14:02,180
Qian.

280
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:03,460
Mr. Guo?

281
00:14:03,600 --> 00:14:03,980
You…

282
00:14:04,480 --> 00:14:04,980
You…

283
00:14:05,510 --> 00:14:06,850
You followed me?

284
00:14:21,960 --> 00:14:22,730
Qian.

285
00:14:23,870 --> 00:14:25,460
Are those two suitcases yours?

286
00:14:25,550 --> 00:14:26,730
What are you two doing here?

287
00:14:26,910 --> 00:14:28,610
Did my mom send you to follow me?

288
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:31,370
Qian, your mom
is really worried about you.

289
00:14:32,360 --> 00:14:33,730
She's not worried.

290
00:14:33,750 --> 00:14:35,100
She just doesn't trust me.

291
00:14:35,120 --> 00:14:37,490
Qian, you shouldn't
think of your mom that way.

292
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:39,060
Have you ever thought

293
00:14:39,510 --> 00:14:40,370
that the world

294
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:43,100
isn't as good as you think it is?

295
00:14:43,440 --> 00:14:45,100
When you were on the phone just now,

296
00:14:45,270 --> 00:14:46,580
we heard you from outside.

297
00:14:46,750 --> 00:14:49,130
One of those suitcases isn't yours.

298
00:14:49,670 --> 00:14:50,770
Someone asked you to carry it.

299
00:14:51,240 --> 00:14:52,650
If I'm not mistaken,

300
00:14:52,750 --> 00:14:53,850
what's inside that suitcase

301
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:55,460
is a helmeted hornbill casque.

302
00:14:56,390 --> 00:14:56,980
Qian.

303
00:14:57,160 --> 00:14:59,340
Smuggling endangered wildlife
or wildlife products

304
00:15:00,240 --> 00:15:01,220
is a criminal offense.

305
00:15:02,640 --> 00:15:03,370
That's impossible.

306
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:05,250
That person would never set me up.

307
00:15:05,640 --> 00:15:07,180
I hope it's not what I think it is.

308
00:15:07,630 --> 00:15:08,340
So,

309
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:10,530
can we open the suitcase and check?

310
00:15:10,630 --> 00:15:12,220
What if it really is
just local souvenirs inside?

311
00:15:12,510 --> 00:15:14,530
If so,

312
00:15:14,550 --> 00:15:16,100
I'll call your mom

313
00:15:16,630 --> 00:15:18,340
and tell her to stop worrying so much.

314
00:15:19,640 --> 00:15:20,180
Deal.

315
00:15:21,030 --> 00:15:23,010
My mom always listens to you anyway.

316
00:15:23,790 --> 00:15:24,300
I trust you.

317
00:15:31,880 --> 00:15:33,250
This is what he asked me to bring.

318
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:17,980
How…

319
00:16:18,040 --> 00:16:18,940
How could this be?

320
00:16:19,640 --> 00:16:20,460
Mr. Guo,

321
00:16:20,520 --> 00:16:21,130
I… I didn't know

322
00:16:21,150 --> 00:16:22,180
what was inside.

323
00:16:22,240 --> 00:16:24,610
Under Criminal Law, Article 341,

324
00:16:24,790 --> 00:16:27,730
buying, transporting, or selling
helmeted hornbill casques

325
00:16:27,750 --> 00:16:29,530
is a criminal offense.
Do you understand?

326
00:16:31,280 --> 00:16:32,060
Mr. Guo,

327
00:16:32,280 --> 00:16:34,100
I… I really didn't know.

328
00:16:34,160 --> 00:16:35,850
I had no idea

329
00:16:35,870 --> 00:16:37,650
what was inside.

330
00:16:51,270 --> 00:16:52,580
Mom!

331
00:16:53,480 --> 00:16:54,180
Qian.

332
00:16:54,870 --> 00:16:57,130
I'm sorry. I messed up.

333
00:17:00,280 --> 00:17:01,610
Mom, I'm so sorry.

334
00:17:01,760 --> 00:17:02,700
I was wrong.

335
00:17:03,270 --> 00:17:05,330
Can you talk to Mr. Guo for me?

336
00:17:06,310 --> 00:17:07,770
I want to help you make this right.

337
00:17:09,070 --> 00:17:10,570
Put Mr. Guo on the phone.

338
00:17:13,510 --> 00:17:14,420
Hello, Deng.

339
00:17:14,720 --> 00:17:15,140
It's me.

340
00:17:15,550 --> 00:17:16,220
Mr. Guo.

341
00:17:17,680 --> 00:17:19,090
I support what Qian wants to do.

342
00:17:20,030 --> 00:17:21,180
Let her make up for this.

343
00:17:22,110 --> 00:17:23,900
I believe in my daughter.

344
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:27,380
And I trust Customs.

345
00:17:29,760 --> 00:17:30,460
Understood.

346
00:17:31,520 --> 00:17:32,770
I'll report it to the Chief.

347
00:17:53,310 --> 00:17:55,330
Can I still talk to you?

348
00:17:55,680 --> 00:17:57,290
Can you be around more?

349
00:17:58,200 --> 00:17:59,180
A father

350
00:17:59,680 --> 00:18:02,180
I only ever get to see online.

351
00:18:02,510 --> 00:18:03,380
A mother

352
00:18:03,960 --> 00:18:05,490
who chose work over her kid.

353
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:07,730
I'm worse off than an orphan.

354
00:18:08,110 --> 00:18:09,660
At least orphans
have someone looking after them.

355
00:18:09,720 --> 00:18:10,700
What about me?

356
00:18:12,440 --> 00:18:13,290
I know.

357
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:15,010
These past few years,

358
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:17,700
we have really upset you.

359
00:18:19,680 --> 00:18:21,770
But your dad and I had our reasons.

360
00:18:22,720 --> 00:18:24,420
You know we love you.

361
00:18:25,440 --> 00:18:25,940
But

362
00:18:27,790 --> 00:18:29,460
we have jobs.

363
00:18:30,070 --> 00:18:32,420
We have work we have to do.

364
00:18:32,790 --> 00:18:34,570
Then why did you even have me?

365
00:18:34,720 --> 00:18:36,660
You just wanted me out of your way!

366
00:18:36,750 --> 00:18:39,810
How can you
still call yourself a mother?

367
00:18:40,280 --> 00:18:40,770
Qian.

368
00:18:41,040 --> 00:18:42,380
Don't touch me!

369
00:18:43,680 --> 00:18:44,420
Qian.

370
00:18:44,790 --> 00:18:45,730
Where are you going?

371
00:18:46,030 --> 00:18:47,530
I'm an adult.

372
00:18:47,760 --> 00:18:49,250
You don't get to control me!

373
00:18:49,270 --> 00:18:51,250
Where I go is none of your business!

374
00:18:55,070 --> 00:18:55,570
Move in.

375
00:19:07,150 --> 00:19:08,250
Yeah, Guo speaking. Go ahead.

376
00:19:12,760 --> 00:19:13,260
Okay.

377
00:19:15,070 --> 00:19:16,020
Got it.

378
00:19:18,160 --> 00:19:18,530
Alright.

379
00:19:19,030 --> 00:19:19,450
Bye.

380
00:19:21,670 --> 00:19:23,330
Qian did great.

381
00:19:23,510 --> 00:19:24,850
Zhou Bing's bringing her over shortly.

382
00:19:25,990 --> 00:19:26,450
Okay.

383
00:19:41,670 --> 00:19:43,410
Come on, Qian. They're over there.

384
00:20:00,280 --> 00:20:01,900
My girl's gotten prettier.

385
00:20:02,030 --> 00:20:03,410
Mom, I'm sorry.

386
00:20:03,430 --> 00:20:04,580
This was all my fault.

387
00:20:06,070 --> 00:20:07,260
Silly girl.

388
00:20:08,280 --> 00:20:10,050
You did so well just now.

389
00:20:10,150 --> 00:20:10,970
You know that?

390
00:20:11,150 --> 00:20:12,300
Good job.

391
00:20:14,870 --> 00:20:15,570
Really.

392
00:20:15,990 --> 00:20:16,620
No more crying.

393
00:20:21,590 --> 00:20:22,180
Mom,

394
00:20:22,680 --> 00:20:25,210
this is a gift I got for you in Myanmar.

395
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:27,900
I bought it with money I earned myself.

396
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:29,570
You bought this for me?

397
00:20:32,510 --> 00:20:33,770
I'll love it for sure.

398
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:35,460
My daughter has great taste.

399
00:20:36,680 --> 00:20:37,620
Thank you, sweetheart.

400
00:20:40,230 --> 00:20:40,820
Alright.

401
00:20:41,070 --> 00:20:41,740
Don't cry.

402
00:20:42,590 --> 00:20:43,380
Deng.

403
00:20:46,070 --> 00:20:46,620
Go.

404
00:20:47,590 --> 00:20:48,660
Do exactly what they say.

405
00:20:50,840 --> 00:20:51,330
Go.

406
00:20:52,040 --> 00:20:52,570
You've got this.

407
00:21:25,070 --> 00:21:25,930
What can I get you?

408
00:21:25,950 --> 00:21:26,460
No need.

409
00:21:26,480 --> 00:21:27,620
I'm here to meet someone.

410
00:21:29,600 --> 00:21:30,210
Li.

411
00:21:31,440 --> 00:21:33,460
Why did you pick

412
00:21:33,550 --> 00:21:34,460
a place like this?

413
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:35,650
And dressed

414
00:21:35,830 --> 00:21:37,140
so low-key, too.

415
00:21:37,920 --> 00:21:39,050
I almost didn't recognize you.

416
00:21:40,720 --> 00:21:41,370
Excuse me,

417
00:21:41,640 --> 00:21:42,900
one pork trotter rice for him.

418
00:21:43,070 --> 00:21:43,490
Sure thing!

419
00:21:43,510 --> 00:21:44,460
No, thanks.

420
00:21:44,550 --> 00:21:47,740
I'm not really used to food like this.

421
00:21:48,480 --> 00:21:49,740
My treat.

422
00:21:51,200 --> 00:21:52,050
Thank you.

423
00:21:54,230 --> 00:21:55,210
Thank you, Li.

424
00:22:02,550 --> 00:22:03,860
Don't come to roadside stalls much, huh?

425
00:22:07,510 --> 00:22:08,810
You foreigners

426
00:22:09,070 --> 00:22:10,620
are all used to knives and forks.

427
00:22:11,550 --> 00:22:12,900
Come on, Li. That's not fair.

428
00:22:17,030 --> 00:22:17,810
You know what?

429
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:20,490
When I first came to Binhai,

430
00:22:20,880 --> 00:22:21,730
I was so broke

431
00:22:21,750 --> 00:22:23,250
that I could only afford
pork trotter rice once a week.

432
00:22:23,640 --> 00:22:24,660
Every time I ate it,

433
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:26,770
it felt like I was rewarding myself.

434
00:22:27,440 --> 00:22:28,810
My biggest dream back then

435
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:31,570
was being able to eat
pork trotter rice every day.

436
00:22:32,550 --> 00:22:33,860
Sounds pathetic, right?

437
00:22:35,880 --> 00:22:36,900
Li,

438
00:22:38,070 --> 00:22:39,900
now you can eat

439
00:22:40,270 --> 00:22:41,050
as much as you want.

440
00:22:41,160 --> 00:22:42,810
But if you people keep doing this,

441
00:22:43,310 --> 00:22:44,570
I'm afraid I won't even be able

442
00:22:45,160 --> 00:22:45,980
to afford one meal.

443
00:22:48,880 --> 00:22:49,490
Li,

444
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:50,860
this time,

445
00:22:50,960 --> 00:22:52,050
I messed up

446
00:22:52,480 --> 00:22:53,900
the hornbill casque shipment.

447
00:22:54,240 --> 00:22:55,090
I assure you,

448
00:22:55,830 --> 00:22:57,140
it won't happen again.

449
00:22:57,400 --> 00:22:58,050
Again?

450
00:22:58,720 --> 00:22:59,980
How much do you think I have left

451
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:00,860
for you to burn through?

452
00:23:01,830 --> 00:23:04,010
What's next? Having me
carry phones through Customs, too?

453
00:23:05,550 --> 00:23:06,700
Li, I'm sorry.

454
00:23:06,790 --> 00:23:08,660
I'm really sorry about it.
You know, that's…

455
00:23:09,070 --> 00:23:10,180
Don't speak English to me!

456
00:23:10,640 --> 00:23:11,140
Sorry.

457
00:23:13,510 --> 00:23:14,220
Li.

458
00:23:14,750 --> 00:23:15,810
Next shipment,

459
00:23:16,750 --> 00:23:17,810
I'll watch it myself.

460
00:23:19,480 --> 00:23:21,900
You still don't get
where you went wrong.

461
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:25,940
In this line of work,

462
00:23:26,550 --> 00:23:27,700
getting cargo seized by Customs

463
00:23:27,720 --> 00:23:28,570
is normal.

464
00:23:29,030 --> 00:23:30,220
But this time,

465
00:23:30,960 --> 00:23:32,530
you didn't just lose your mules.

466
00:23:32,720 --> 00:23:33,860
You even lost

467
00:23:34,200 --> 00:23:34,980
your handler.

468
00:23:35,590 --> 00:23:37,140
If they trace it back to you,

469
00:23:37,350 --> 00:23:38,620
- and drag me in… - Li.

470
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:39,940
Don't worry.

471
00:23:40,550 --> 00:23:41,730
It won't happen.

472
00:23:42,110 --> 00:23:43,050
You see,

473
00:23:43,200 --> 00:23:44,010
James

474
00:23:44,270 --> 00:23:45,050
and his people

475
00:23:45,070 --> 00:23:47,660
are all part
of an overseas trafficking ring.

476
00:23:47,920 --> 00:23:49,570
I only contact them

477
00:23:49,960 --> 00:23:52,250
through special channels.

478
00:23:52,830 --> 00:23:53,620
And

479
00:23:53,960 --> 00:23:54,620
all the payments

480
00:23:54,830 --> 00:23:56,330
I make to them

481
00:23:56,920 --> 00:23:58,010
are done in cryptocurrency.

482
00:23:58,830 --> 00:24:00,090
They can't get to me or you.

483
00:24:02,590 --> 00:24:03,700
That would be best.

484
00:24:05,030 --> 00:24:06,420
But let me make this clear.

485
00:24:06,960 --> 00:24:08,330
If they get to you,

486
00:24:08,510 --> 00:24:10,980
I'll do whatever it takes
to protect myself.

487
00:24:12,830 --> 00:24:14,810
The reason I asked you here today

488
00:24:15,070 --> 00:24:16,250
is to tell you one thing:

489
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:17,810
I can still make a living

490
00:24:18,030 --> 00:24:19,050
in this business for now.

491
00:24:19,960 --> 00:24:21,180
But if anyone

492
00:24:21,480 --> 00:24:22,940
tries to send me back to those days

493
00:24:22,960 --> 00:24:24,810
when I could only
afford one decent meal a week,

494
00:24:26,640 --> 00:24:27,620
I don't care who it is.

495
00:24:28,160 --> 00:24:29,570
I won't let them off.

496
00:24:30,510 --> 00:24:31,460
Not you,

497
00:24:31,960 --> 00:24:33,700
and not Mr. E either.

498
00:24:33,830 --> 00:24:34,330
Li,

499
00:24:34,400 --> 00:24:35,090
I understand.

500
00:24:35,200 --> 00:24:35,940
I really do.

501
00:24:35,960 --> 00:24:38,050
Not just that, I need you
to remember it.

502
00:24:38,920 --> 00:24:39,700
Yes.

503
00:24:39,720 --> 00:24:40,530
I'll remember.

504
00:24:42,110 --> 00:24:42,730
Li.

505
00:24:42,830 --> 00:24:43,700
Both times now,

506
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:45,380
our deal…

507
00:24:46,200 --> 00:24:48,530
got ruined by that

508
00:24:49,030 --> 00:24:50,010
Section I guy,

509
00:24:50,030 --> 00:24:51,010
Guo Cong.

510
00:24:51,960 --> 00:24:52,730
So,

511
00:24:53,960 --> 00:24:55,010
should we…

512
00:24:55,030 --> 00:24:55,900
Don't do anything stupid.

513
00:24:56,590 --> 00:24:57,420
I'm warning you.

514
00:24:58,310 --> 00:25:00,490
Back then, Sa Ziyi
went after Chen Sanhe.

515
00:25:00,590 --> 00:25:02,380
That's what made Customs go all in

516
00:25:02,400 --> 00:25:03,290
and take her down.

517
00:25:05,270 --> 00:25:06,570
As for Guo Cong,

518
00:25:07,830 --> 00:25:08,940
have someone keep an eye on him.

519
00:25:09,720 --> 00:25:10,980
We'll play it by ear.

520
00:25:13,310 --> 00:25:14,180
Sit down.

521
00:25:17,790 --> 00:25:18,730
Finish your meal.

522
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:19,770
Don't waste it.

523
00:25:20,270 --> 00:25:22,980
Enjoy every bite
of that pork trotter rice.

524
00:25:23,480 --> 00:25:23,900
Yes.

525
00:25:24,880 --> 00:25:25,660
I will.

526
00:25:48,030 --> 00:25:50,290
Here we go! Food's coming!

527
00:25:50,310 --> 00:25:52,010
Let's dig in!

528
00:25:52,030 --> 00:25:53,220
Mentor, food's ready! Come on!

529
00:25:53,310 --> 00:25:54,420
Let's go.

530
00:25:54,510 --> 00:25:55,180
Time to eat.

531
00:25:55,200 --> 00:25:56,490
Come eat, Deng!

532
00:25:56,550 --> 00:25:57,330
- Alright. - Here.

533
00:25:57,790 --> 00:25:58,250
Your spoon.

534
00:25:58,350 --> 00:25:59,620
- I already got yours. - Thanks.

535
00:26:00,070 --> 00:26:00,700
Thanks.

536
00:26:10,440 --> 00:26:11,380
I don't think

537
00:26:12,720 --> 00:26:14,380
I've ever made soup for Qian.

538
00:26:18,110 --> 00:26:19,490
I always thought it took too long.

539
00:26:20,720 --> 00:26:21,140
Too much hassle.

540
00:26:24,070 --> 00:26:25,490
I really am a terrible mother.

541
00:26:27,590 --> 00:26:28,380
Deng,

542
00:26:29,160 --> 00:26:30,660
Qian's situation

543
00:26:30,920 --> 00:26:32,810
still hasn't been finalized.

544
00:26:32,880 --> 00:26:34,620
Don't think too much about it.

545
00:26:34,750 --> 00:26:36,220
Yeah, don't overthink it.

546
00:26:39,960 --> 00:26:40,490
Zhang Yu,

547
00:26:41,480 --> 00:26:42,050
Xiaoyan,

548
00:26:43,400 --> 00:26:44,330
thank you.

549
00:26:46,270 --> 00:26:47,730
I know you've been worried.

550
00:26:48,310 --> 00:26:49,810
These past few days at home,

551
00:26:51,070 --> 00:26:52,460
I've thought it through.

552
00:26:53,200 --> 00:26:55,940
I've submitted a transfer request

553
00:26:55,960 --> 00:26:57,180
and applied for leave.

554
00:26:58,440 --> 00:26:59,700
Don't try to talk me out of it.

555
00:27:00,680 --> 00:27:01,940
I've made up my mind.

556
00:27:02,270 --> 00:27:03,900
I want to use this time off

557
00:27:04,400 --> 00:27:06,460
to take Qian back
to my hometown for a couple of weeks.

558
00:27:07,110 --> 00:27:08,490
After everything she's been through,

559
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:10,730
I want to give her a change of scenery

560
00:27:11,510 --> 00:27:13,380
and help her get back on her feet.

561
00:27:13,480 --> 00:27:14,330
And also,

562
00:27:14,550 --> 00:27:16,490
I want more time

563
00:27:17,030 --> 00:27:17,940
to be with my family.

564
00:27:18,070 --> 00:27:19,090
And with my husband.

565
00:27:19,440 --> 00:27:21,090
Qian's dad is back now, too.

566
00:27:21,640 --> 00:27:22,620
Our family

567
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:24,090
finally feels like a real home again.

568
00:27:25,440 --> 00:27:27,010
So no matter what happens with Qian,

569
00:27:28,070 --> 00:27:29,220
we'll be there for her.

570
00:27:31,750 --> 00:27:32,530
Can you understand that?

571
00:27:35,640 --> 00:27:36,380
We understand.

572
00:27:38,750 --> 00:27:39,330
Alright.

573
00:27:40,400 --> 00:27:41,090
Let's eat.

574
00:27:41,920 --> 00:27:42,420
Eat up.

575
00:27:42,680 --> 00:27:43,010
Here.

576
00:27:44,510 --> 00:27:47,010
Let's try Zhang Yu's cooking.

577
00:27:48,200 --> 00:27:48,980
Here, braised pork.

578
00:27:49,070 --> 00:27:50,180
Let's see how it is.

579
00:27:53,550 --> 00:27:54,460
- Good! - Is it spicy?

580
00:27:54,480 --> 00:27:55,290
Tastes great.

581
00:27:55,640 --> 00:27:57,330
I was worried
it might be too spicy for you.

582
00:27:57,590 --> 00:27:58,250
It's perfect.

583
00:27:58,270 --> 00:28:00,050
Why don't you cook for us more often?

584
00:28:00,750 --> 00:28:02,570
Like I ever have the time
or the setup for that.

585
00:28:02,680 --> 00:28:03,490
Come on.

586
00:28:07,400 --> 00:28:08,860
Deng's transfer

587
00:28:09,480 --> 00:28:10,290
has been approved.

588
00:28:11,110 --> 00:28:12,570
All the paperwork is done.

589
00:28:15,110 --> 00:28:17,290
She wants to treat
everyone to dinner tonight

590
00:28:17,440 --> 00:28:18,180
to thank us all.

591
00:28:18,720 --> 00:28:20,140
She'll send the time and place

592
00:28:20,160 --> 00:28:20,810
later today.

593
00:28:22,640 --> 00:28:23,420
Zhang Yu, Xiaoyan,

594
00:28:23,880 --> 00:28:25,380
help pack up Deng's things later.

595
00:28:25,440 --> 00:28:26,050
Then, we'll go pick her up.

596
00:28:28,960 --> 00:28:30,460
Alright, see you tonight.

597
00:28:32,440 --> 00:28:33,490
One more thing.

598
00:28:34,510 --> 00:28:35,660
At dinner tonight,

599
00:28:35,960 --> 00:28:36,620
no getting all sentimental.

600
00:28:47,880 --> 00:28:49,900
One, two, three, four, five, six.

601
00:28:49,920 --> 00:28:51,980
How did Cong manage to find

602
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:54,050
a restaurant with ocean views
on three sides?

603
00:28:55,030 --> 00:28:56,700
Bowen, any progress?

604
00:28:56,720 --> 00:28:57,530
Got it.

605
00:28:57,550 --> 00:28:58,770
Man, the abalone over there looks good.

606
00:28:58,790 --> 00:28:59,420
Order it.

607
00:28:59,440 --> 00:28:59,940
Right there.

608
00:29:02,110 --> 00:29:02,940
Cong,

609
00:29:03,440 --> 00:29:05,380
you know a good place like this?

610
00:29:05,880 --> 00:29:07,140
My mentor found it.

611
00:29:09,200 --> 00:29:11,290
This is where he first
took me out for a meal.

612
00:29:12,480 --> 00:29:13,660
How's your mentor doing?

613
00:29:14,400 --> 00:29:15,860
I left in such a hurry this time.

614
00:29:16,200 --> 00:29:17,730
I didn't even get a chance to visit him.

615
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:19,220
He's in good health,

616
00:29:19,400 --> 00:29:20,730
but his memory keeps getting worse.

617
00:29:20,790 --> 00:29:21,770
He's forgotten many things.

618
00:29:24,030 --> 00:29:25,140
- Maybe that's for the best. - Careful.

619
00:29:25,400 --> 00:29:26,290
Sometimes forgetting is better.

620
00:29:27,680 --> 00:29:29,140
He probably doesn't even remember me.

621
00:29:29,510 --> 00:29:30,460
Here they come.

622
00:29:32,200 --> 00:29:33,770
- Hold the rail. - Slow down. Easy.

623
00:29:34,270 --> 00:29:36,290
I told you to go check what's good here!

624
00:29:36,400 --> 00:29:37,010
Right?

625
00:29:37,030 --> 00:29:37,730
Dayu.

626
00:29:37,920 --> 00:29:38,420
Coming!

627
00:29:38,440 --> 00:29:40,050
A host shows up late? Really?

628
00:29:41,240 --> 00:29:42,900
We were packing things up.

629
00:29:42,920 --> 00:29:44,220
It took a bit longer.

630
00:29:44,830 --> 00:29:45,620
Deng, slow down.

631
00:29:45,640 --> 00:29:46,490
Okay.

632
00:29:46,550 --> 00:29:47,330
Deng,

633
00:29:47,790 --> 00:29:49,330
I wasn't talking about you.

634
00:29:49,830 --> 00:29:51,220
I meant him.

635
00:29:51,240 --> 00:29:52,940
Cong's paying tonight, no arguments.

636
00:29:53,720 --> 00:29:54,980
Nobody's leaving hungry.

637
00:29:55,310 --> 00:29:57,180
- Nice place. - Is everyone here?

638
00:29:57,350 --> 00:29:58,140
[Yuren Restaurant]
No, not yet.

639
00:29:58,550 --> 00:30:00,090
We're still missing one.

640
00:30:00,270 --> 00:30:02,530
Shihuo's probably trying
to get permission from his wife.

641
00:30:06,480 --> 00:30:07,540
Great place, Cong.

642
00:30:08,280 --> 00:30:10,380
Is everyone here?
Then I'll start serving!

643
00:30:10,400 --> 00:30:11,770
Sure! Here, let me take that.

644
00:30:13,640 --> 00:30:14,250
Zhang,

645
00:30:14,640 --> 00:30:15,620
you know this place well.

646
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:17,300
Help me get everyone settled.

647
00:30:17,430 --> 00:30:17,980
Okay.

648
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:19,410
Help yourselves to drinks.

649
00:30:19,510 --> 00:30:20,730
Alright, leave it to me.

650
00:30:21,400 --> 00:30:22,410
Thank you, Fei.

651
00:30:23,360 --> 00:30:24,450
Hey, can you grab that for me?

652
00:30:25,310 --> 00:30:26,060
Cong.

653
00:30:26,270 --> 00:30:26,570
What's up?

654
00:30:26,590 --> 00:30:27,660
That's not cool.

655
00:30:28,400 --> 00:30:30,250
You brought Zhang Yu here,

656
00:30:30,270 --> 00:30:31,220
but not us.

657
00:30:31,240 --> 00:30:32,730
Who are the rest of us to you?

658
00:30:32,750 --> 00:30:33,660
Dayu.

659
00:30:35,200 --> 00:30:36,370
This is

660
00:30:37,200 --> 00:30:40,220
where I became Mr. Guo's trainee

661
00:30:40,240 --> 00:30:42,290
and where Mr. Guo
became Mr. Chen's trainee.

662
00:30:42,800 --> 00:30:45,370
This place is sacred to me.

663
00:30:45,670 --> 00:30:47,930
Letting you all in here for free

664
00:30:47,950 --> 00:30:49,690
is already a big stretch.

665
00:30:50,390 --> 00:30:51,420
I'll take that.

666
00:30:52,590 --> 00:30:54,050
I heard that, Cong.

667
00:30:54,270 --> 00:30:54,740
What?

668
00:30:54,760 --> 00:30:57,250
Zhang Yu said it's free for us!

669
00:30:57,520 --> 00:30:58,570
Bowen,

670
00:30:59,160 --> 00:31:01,330
order that lobster.

671
00:31:01,350 --> 00:31:02,820
- Steamed with garlic. Go! - Got it.

672
00:31:06,270 --> 00:31:07,330
Sure, hand it over.

673
00:31:07,480 --> 00:31:08,210
Let me rinse it.

674
00:31:08,230 --> 00:31:09,100
Alright, pass me one.

675
00:31:09,200 --> 00:31:10,580
Here, right here!

676
00:31:11,200 --> 00:31:11,770
Nice.

677
00:31:11,960 --> 00:31:13,050
- Sit. - Have a seat, Deng.

678
00:31:13,070 --> 00:31:14,020
The ratings are great.

679
00:31:14,040 --> 00:31:16,380
Listen, nobody's paying tonight
except me.

680
00:31:16,400 --> 00:31:17,100
Understood?

681
00:31:17,120 --> 00:31:18,180
This one's on me.

682
00:31:18,200 --> 00:31:20,460
No way. Tonight, Cong is paying, period.

683
00:31:22,840 --> 00:31:23,940
Come on, last one.

684
00:31:23,960 --> 00:31:24,690
Last dish coming up.

685
00:31:24,710 --> 00:31:25,460
Here's another one.

686
00:31:25,480 --> 00:31:26,180
Careful. It's soup.

687
00:31:26,510 --> 00:31:27,490
Alright.

688
00:31:28,510 --> 00:31:29,770
Okay.

689
00:31:30,320 --> 00:31:31,490
Everything's here.

690
00:31:32,430 --> 00:31:33,300
Shihuo!

691
00:31:33,680 --> 00:31:34,380
I'm so sorry!

692
00:31:34,400 --> 00:31:36,050
Couldn't get the night off
from your wife?

693
00:31:36,630 --> 00:31:37,580
Sorry, I'm late.

694
00:31:37,600 --> 00:31:38,410
Deng, I'm sorry.

695
00:31:38,560 --> 00:31:39,490
Not late at all.

696
00:31:39,510 --> 00:31:40,740
Perfect timing. We haven't started.

697
00:31:40,760 --> 00:31:41,410
Right, not yet.

698
00:31:41,430 --> 00:31:42,410
Come! Take a seat!

699
00:31:42,480 --> 00:31:43,660
Feng Ning heard you were leaving

700
00:31:43,680 --> 00:31:44,770
and came with me to get you a gift.

701
00:31:44,790 --> 00:31:45,490
That's why I'm late.

702
00:31:45,870 --> 00:31:47,100
What's this for?

703
00:31:48,400 --> 00:31:49,460
I appreciate the thought,

704
00:31:49,480 --> 00:31:50,300
but I can't accept the gift.

705
00:31:52,840 --> 00:31:53,490
Just take it.

706
00:31:53,510 --> 00:31:54,380
Deng!

707
00:31:54,600 --> 00:31:55,210
Take it.

708
00:31:55,430 --> 00:31:56,300
If you don't,

709
00:31:56,320 --> 00:31:57,540
he'll have to answer to his wife.

710
00:31:58,270 --> 00:32:00,610
Stop making his wife
sound like some kind of monster.

711
00:32:01,430 --> 00:32:03,770
Being married to someone
in Customs is hard enough.

712
00:32:04,560 --> 00:32:05,690
Have a seat!

713
00:32:09,710 --> 00:32:10,250
Sit here.

714
00:32:10,350 --> 00:32:10,850
Sure.

715
00:32:11,400 --> 00:32:11,690
Everybody,

716
00:32:11,950 --> 00:32:12,980
let's eat!

717
00:32:13,950 --> 00:32:15,020
- Eat! - Let's get started!

718
00:32:16,040 --> 00:32:16,300
Here.

719
00:32:16,550 --> 00:32:16,980
Thank you.

720
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:17,420
Try it.

721
00:32:19,040 --> 00:32:19,650
Try one of these.

722
00:32:19,830 --> 00:32:20,330
Nice.

723
00:32:20,670 --> 00:32:21,140
So good!

724
00:32:21,160 --> 00:32:21,420
Okay.

725
00:32:22,160 --> 00:32:23,260
The food here is good.

726
00:32:24,760 --> 00:32:25,370
Eat, eat.

727
00:32:25,790 --> 00:32:26,420
Delicious!

728
00:32:27,040 --> 00:32:28,580
Shihuo, pass me some of those shreds.

729
00:32:29,230 --> 00:32:29,810
Mentor.

730
00:32:32,600 --> 00:32:33,610
This toast is for you.

731
00:32:33,790 --> 00:32:34,650
This past year,

732
00:32:34,670 --> 00:32:36,020
thank you for everything
you've done for me.

733
00:32:36,160 --> 00:32:37,300
If it weren't for you

734
00:32:37,550 --> 00:32:39,020
helping me find where I shine,

735
00:32:40,040 --> 00:32:40,860
I think

736
00:32:42,670 --> 00:32:44,330
I'd still be the weakest link
in Section I.

737
00:32:44,830 --> 00:32:45,770
That's not true.

738
00:32:46,790 --> 00:32:47,460
Sit.

739
00:32:47,790 --> 00:32:49,050
I want to thank you, too.

740
00:32:50,510 --> 00:32:51,810
During the two years Qian was abroad,

741
00:32:52,670 --> 00:32:54,740
you were the one
keeping me company most of the time.

742
00:32:54,830 --> 00:32:56,020
That's why I never felt too alone.

743
00:32:56,880 --> 00:32:57,210
Alright.

744
00:32:57,630 --> 00:32:58,610
Now that I'm leaving,

745
00:32:59,040 --> 00:33:01,020
maybe you'll finally have time
to date someone.

746
00:33:02,230 --> 00:33:03,900
I'm still so young.

747
00:33:03,920 --> 00:33:04,860
Why would I be dating?

748
00:33:04,880 --> 00:33:05,860
Oh, you're definitely at that age.

749
00:33:05,880 --> 00:33:06,610
Hurry up and find someone.

750
00:33:07,200 --> 00:33:08,140
Zhang Yu,

751
00:33:08,230 --> 00:33:09,210
go get me a beer.

752
00:33:09,630 --> 00:33:10,490
A beer?

753
00:33:11,670 --> 00:33:12,860
You all have rules to follow,

754
00:33:12,880 --> 00:33:14,140
but I don't right now.

755
00:33:14,390 --> 00:33:15,050
I want one.

756
00:33:15,110 --> 00:33:15,580
Go.

757
00:33:15,600 --> 00:33:16,050
Get me one.

758
00:33:16,600 --> 00:33:17,580
I'll get it for you.

759
00:33:17,600 --> 00:33:18,900
You don't know where it is. I'll go.

760
00:33:18,920 --> 00:33:19,700
I saw it.

761
00:33:19,830 --> 00:33:21,090
It's fine. I've got it.

762
00:33:22,630 --> 00:33:23,980
Where did I put that bottle opener?

763
00:33:24,230 --> 00:33:25,330
Over here.

764
00:33:26,630 --> 00:33:27,090
Here!

765
00:33:27,110 --> 00:33:27,810
Right here!

766
00:33:27,830 --> 00:33:28,650
Here, the opener.

767
00:33:28,670 --> 00:33:28,980
Okay.

768
00:33:32,320 --> 00:33:33,810
Pour the beer.

769
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:38,610
Alright.

770
00:33:39,600 --> 00:33:40,530
Here, Xiaoyan.

771
00:33:41,110 --> 00:33:41,930
Keep it up.

772
00:33:42,390 --> 00:33:42,900
Go for it.

773
00:33:48,670 --> 00:33:49,300
Alright.

774
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:51,610
Zhang Yu,

775
00:33:52,600 --> 00:33:53,090
Bowen.

776
00:33:53,440 --> 00:33:53,740
Here.

777
00:33:55,920 --> 00:33:57,020
Easy, easy.

778
00:33:57,230 --> 00:33:58,140
This one is for both of you.

779
00:33:58,230 --> 00:33:59,420
Sit down!

780
00:33:59,440 --> 00:34:00,610
Why are you standing?

781
00:34:00,830 --> 00:34:01,580
Sit.

782
00:34:03,920 --> 00:34:04,980
You two

783
00:34:05,110 --> 00:34:06,460
are a bit older than Xiaoyan.

784
00:34:07,040 --> 00:34:07,980
From now on,

785
00:34:08,230 --> 00:34:09,580
look out for her a little more.

786
00:34:09,600 --> 00:34:10,460
Don't let her mess up.

787
00:34:10,720 --> 00:34:11,370
Can you do that?

788
00:34:11,630 --> 00:34:13,020
I'm fine with Yu keeping me in line.

789
00:34:13,200 --> 00:34:15,020
But this guy's only
a few months older than me.

790
00:34:15,200 --> 00:34:16,610
Why should I listen to him?

791
00:34:16,830 --> 00:34:18,330
He's more mature and steadier than you.

792
00:34:18,950 --> 00:34:19,900
That's enough.

793
00:34:21,190 --> 00:34:21,650
Deng,

794
00:34:22,480 --> 00:34:24,850
Xiaoyan and I will learn
and grow together.

795
00:34:25,430 --> 00:34:25,650
Good.

796
00:34:25,840 --> 00:34:27,170
Who said I want to grow with you?

797
00:34:27,230 --> 00:34:28,700
Deng, don't worry.

798
00:34:28,920 --> 00:34:30,260
We'll look out for Xiaoyan.

799
00:34:30,430 --> 00:34:30,700
Alright.

800
00:34:30,720 --> 00:34:31,060
Here.

801
00:34:32,040 --> 00:34:32,530
Cheers.

802
00:34:36,640 --> 00:34:37,260
Bottoms up?

803
00:34:38,520 --> 00:34:41,290
- Easy. - Easy.

804
00:34:43,680 --> 00:34:44,060
So,

805
00:34:44,120 --> 00:34:44,650
Shihuo,

806
00:34:45,120 --> 00:34:46,090
let me have a drink with you.

807
00:34:48,520 --> 00:34:49,380
You

808
00:34:49,440 --> 00:34:50,650
may not say much,

809
00:34:50,790 --> 00:34:52,410
but with your military background,

810
00:34:52,560 --> 00:34:54,090
you're the most meticulous one here.

811
00:34:54,440 --> 00:34:56,530
You think everything through
before you act.

812
00:34:57,110 --> 00:34:58,620
Unlike Dayu and Cong,

813
00:34:58,670 --> 00:34:59,770
who are still reckless sometimes.

814
00:35:01,350 --> 00:35:02,620
From here on, Section I

815
00:35:03,110 --> 00:35:05,330
needs you to be its backbone.

816
00:35:06,230 --> 00:35:06,580
I will.

817
00:35:06,870 --> 00:35:07,210
Cheers.

818
00:35:07,560 --> 00:35:08,170
This one's for you.

819
00:35:11,790 --> 00:35:12,620
Deng,

820
00:35:12,680 --> 00:35:14,020
it was years ago

821
00:35:14,080 --> 00:35:15,700
when Cong and I went reckless.

822
00:35:15,870 --> 00:35:16,900
Why are you still bringing it up?

823
00:35:19,550 --> 00:35:20,770
Dayu, you know what?

824
00:35:21,640 --> 00:35:23,090
When I first joined Customs,

825
00:35:23,560 --> 00:35:24,650
I knew your father.

826
00:35:25,680 --> 00:35:27,410
You're not like him.

827
00:35:27,640 --> 00:35:28,940
He was steady.

828
00:35:29,200 --> 00:35:29,900
You're talkative.

829
00:35:31,310 --> 00:35:31,900
True.

830
00:35:33,640 --> 00:35:36,170
But in some ways,
you're exactly like him.

831
00:35:37,080 --> 00:35:37,970
Both are excellent Customs officers.

832
00:35:40,200 --> 00:35:41,290
Dayu,

833
00:35:41,790 --> 00:35:42,500
you're kind.

834
00:35:43,190 --> 00:35:45,060
You always care about how others feel.

835
00:35:45,350 --> 00:35:46,380
Just look at tonight.

836
00:35:47,750 --> 00:35:49,970
You've been keeping things light
the whole time,

837
00:35:50,350 --> 00:35:51,900
so nobody feels too weighed down.

838
00:35:52,750 --> 00:35:53,530
Thank you.

839
00:35:54,190 --> 00:35:55,970
I'm just good at joking around.

840
00:35:57,120 --> 00:35:57,820
No, seriously.

841
00:35:57,990 --> 00:35:59,530
You've got something

842
00:35:59,550 --> 00:36:02,090
that neither Cong nor Shihuo has:

843
00:36:02,440 --> 00:36:03,970
you know how to laugh at yourself.

844
00:36:04,440 --> 00:36:05,140
Seriously.

845
00:36:05,190 --> 00:36:06,770
That is a real skill.

846
00:36:06,790 --> 00:36:07,530
I

847
00:36:07,680 --> 00:36:09,900
have always held myself
too tightly in life.

848
00:36:10,230 --> 00:36:11,700
That's why I couldn't balance

849
00:36:11,760 --> 00:36:13,090
work and family.

850
00:36:16,680 --> 00:36:17,060
Here.

851
00:36:17,320 --> 00:36:19,060
From now on, I'll learn from you.

852
00:36:19,230 --> 00:36:19,730
Dayu.

853
00:36:20,790 --> 00:36:21,380
Cheers.

854
00:36:27,440 --> 00:36:29,140
- Take it easy! - Slow down!

855
00:36:29,320 --> 00:36:29,970
Easy.

856
00:36:39,350 --> 00:36:40,020
Cong.

857
00:36:41,680 --> 00:36:42,090
Cheers.

858
00:36:42,520 --> 00:36:43,620
There's something I want to ask you.

859
00:36:45,560 --> 00:36:46,060
Go ahead.

860
00:36:48,190 --> 00:36:49,820
I want to know if what happened to Qian

861
00:36:50,560 --> 00:36:52,060
has anything to do with Group E.

862
00:36:58,190 --> 00:36:59,460
All I can tell you

